Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.07,0:08:35.07,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I, Giorno Giovanna, have a righteous dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.62,0:08:47.25,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Two years ago, I was struck by an arrow like that one \N and gained my Stand ability. {what's amazing is they have the time to do exposition and still come up with a plan}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.25,0:08:51.34,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,If you're struck by the arrow \N and an ability doesn't awaken within you, you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.34,0:08:53.38,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Awaken within you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.38,0:08:54.43,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.43,0:08:57.85,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,That's what it meant when it said \N "worthy of being chosen"!{What Black Sabbath described OLD MAN as. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.85,0:08:59.76,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,One whose Stand has awakened!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.76,0:09:03.98,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,That must be the motive behind Polpo's test!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.44,0:09:06.27,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I don't know the origin{He literally uses the English word "roots", but that might be a bit less immediately understandable? -Starfish} of the arrow... {I think "origin" sounds better here. Recommend just treating it as wasei-eigo -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.27,0:09:10.61,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,...but I've encountered this same \N type of Stand once before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.23,0:09:14.03,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,It's a long-range, remote controlled Stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.36,0:09:16.41,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Long-range and remote controlled?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.41,0:09:19.03,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,It can only do predetermined, \N simple actions, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.03,0:09:22.12,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,...it won't stop attacking until \N it's done what it was instructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.12,0:09:25.41,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Our best bet is to find its user \N and take them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.00,0:09:28.75,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, that's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.75,0:09:31.67,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Its user is imprisoned. \N There's simply no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.92,0:09:34.13,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.13,0:09:37.13,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It can't leave the shadow \N of the school building right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.13,0:09:40.10,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...so let's circle around to \N the other side while we still can.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.10,0:09:43.10,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Once we're there, before the sun completely sets...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.10,0:09:46.27,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...we'll lure it into the shadow of a moving object...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.27,0:09:48.06,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...then quickly get rid of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.06,0:09:51.77,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,That will force it into direct sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.77,0:09:52.94,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.29,0:10:07.62,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I-It's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.54,0:10:12.50,Main,Black Sabbath,0,0,0,,I have you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.50,0:10:14.05,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.76,0:10:18.59,Main,Black Sabbath,0,0,0,,You witnessed the lighter being relit, did you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.68,0:10:20.76,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,The crows!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.76,0:10:25.52,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,It left the shadow of the school building \N by hiding in the shadows of those flying crows!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.52,0:10:27.14,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Th-That's...{こいつ again... is this more like "Why you...!"? For some reason this just sounds weird, even with the follow up -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.73,0:10:28.98,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Pointless!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.23,0:10:33.90,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,N-No!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.90,0:10:37.78,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It really {\i1}is{\i0} faster and stronger \N in the shadows!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.78,0:10:40.87,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Act 3! 3 Freeze!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.07,0:10:47.25,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,My Echoes Act 3 has the ability to \N make Stands and other things heavier!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.25,0:10:49.17,Main,Echoes,0,0,0,,I have made its hands heavier...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.17,0:10:52.38,Main,Echoes,0,0,0,,...so that it will be unable to lift \N even a finger from the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.30,0:10:59.22,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Its fingers should give out at any second!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.22,0:11:02.30,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I made both of its hands heavier!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.30,0:11:04.89,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,It shouldn't be able to \N bend its fingers anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.89,0:11:06.56,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I-It's so strong...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.56,0:11:09.44,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It's determined to hold onto me \N no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.44,0:11:12.94,Main,Black Sabbath,0,0,0,,Two paths lie before you.{Black Sabbath? Moar liek Broken Record amirite? Still the same phrasing. -Starfish}{drives home the fact that this is a remote-controlled stand, I think. Recall that SHA could only say コッチヲミロ -JMFW} {No u}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.94,0:11:14.11,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,I-It's no use! {Koichi is now Silver}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.11,0:11:17.44,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,Any damage inflicted on a Stand \N goes right back to its user!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.44,0:11:21.03,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,If this keeps up, \N Giorno's legs are gonna shatter!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.03,0:11:23.78,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Act 3! Undo 3 Freeze...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.03,0:11:23.78,Secondary,Giorno,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.78,0:11:26.24,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Don't do that, Koichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.24,0:11:30.87,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Your ability to make things heavier... \N Don't you dare undo it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.87,0:11:32.21,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,This is what I needed. {I don't know if he really expresses "need" so much as this is just something he can use to his advantage. TLC? -JMFW}{I think it's fine, tbh. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.92,0:11:36.09,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,This ability you've brought with you \N is just what I needed! {see previous line's comment -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.09,0:11:38.51,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,But your leg's gonna break!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.76,0:11:45.26,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.26,0:11:46.64,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,That tree...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.64,0:11:50.81,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Gold Experience has the ability to \N continuously imbue objects with life...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.81,0:11:56.61,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...so it made the tree live \N a full life until it withered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.61,0:11:58.48,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Ability?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.48,0:12:01.15,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,But that tree is at least \N ten meters away...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.95,0:12:05.32,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Did you dig a hole to \N touch the tree's roots? {delete "up" -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.00,0:12:19.13,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Y-You did it! \N The shadow is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.13,0:12:21.47,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,You dragged it out into the sunlight!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.56,0:12:32.69,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,You said two paths lay before me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.69,0:12:35.81,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...but for you, there's only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.81,0:12:40.32,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Excuse me Koichi{who now has only brows and eye sockets}, \N but could you move a bit to the right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.32,0:12:42.07,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Huh? Like this? {LS and Jules' cringe count this episodio: 2} {No u}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.87,0:12:50.33,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Muda Muda Muda Muda!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.95,0:12:54.25,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Bask in the sunlight! {Taste the sun -bill wurtz}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.25,0:12:57.00,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,That was your only way forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.00,0:12:58.96,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Your one and only path.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.31,0:13:16.23,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I wonder if I'll be \N allowed in the gang after all this...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.81,0:13:18.02,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,What to do...
Comment: 0,0:13:20.98,0:13:20.98,Main,,0,0,0,,C {Shifted FORWARD 23 frames}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.41,0:13:29.41,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,That arrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.74,0:13:34.50,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,The fact that there's an arrow in Italy \N means there will be even more victims!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.91,0:13:37.25,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I need to tell Mr. Jotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.54,0:13:41.92,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Wh-What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.92,0:13:44.76,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Did you just say there will be more?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.76,0:13:46.76,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Polpo's Stand had the arrow, \N and we defeated it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.76,0:13:48.59,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,You saw it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.59,0:13:52.18,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Defeated? \N You couldn't be more wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.18,0:13:56.10,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I'll admit we were able to \N escape its attacks thanks to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.10,0:14:00.86,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,...but the only reason it stopped was \N because it was forced into the sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.86,0:14:03.23,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,The user wasn't hurt at all! \N They're fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.23,0:14:05.49,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,So Polpo is still alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.49,0:14:11.45,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Not only is he still alive, but we probably didn't even \N hurt him since he has a long-ranged, remote controlled Stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.87,0:14:14.91,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I doubt he even knows \N there was a battle here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.91,0:14:16.62,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.62,0:14:19.63,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,So he really doesn't know what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.63,0:14:21.25,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,He doesn't know I'm a Stand user?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.25,0:14:22.50,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Enough questions!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.50,0:14:26.84,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,If anything, he only would have \N noticed his hands getting heavier...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.84,0:14:30.89,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,...but there's no way he could have figured out \N that you and I are already Stand users.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.30,0:14:36.02,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,So excuse me, \N but can you please move your finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.02,0:14:39.56,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, \N but I can't allow you to make that call.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.56,0:14:42.56,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'm begging you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.56,0:14:45.73,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,This isn't about a single enemy. \N He's part of an organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.73,0:14:49.53,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,If you tell someone, \N the organization may find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.53,0:14:50.78,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.78,0:14:51.99,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Organization?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.70,0:14:55.49,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,You're the only person \N I'll speak of this to, Koichi. {I feel like it'd be in character for Giorno to avoid ending his line with a preposition ("You're the only person to which I'll speak of this, Koichi.") but very YMMV. - Toa} {"You're man mow vog?" -Axel}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.76,0:15:16.89,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Someone delivered me a special-order pizza.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.83,0:15:41.08,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Sorry to have kept you waiting. \N Let's see, your name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.42,0:15:46.21,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Giorno... Giorno, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.21,0:15:47.75,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Giorno Giovanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.09,0:15:51.51,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Ah, yes. My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.51,0:15:55.35,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Eating tends to make me lightheaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.93,0:15:59.73,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,I think all the blood in my body \N rushes to my stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.14,0:16:08.32,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,This may seem like an odd question, \N but are you a man of faith, Giorno?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.69,0:16:13.28,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Well... I wouldn't say I'm particularly devout.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.99,0:16:20.62,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,What I'm about to tell you \N may go against God's word...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.29,0:16:24.00,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,...but I would appreciate it \N if you heeded my words.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.00,0:16:28.55,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,If the most important thing \N in the world is trustworthiness... {POL POL POL}{He really likes going on that board, huh? - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.55,0:16:33.09,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,...then the most despicable thing \N one can do is abuse that trust. {Added "the" after "then." -Axel}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.09,0:16:37.68,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Hear me well. \N To abuse one's trust...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.68,0:16:41.28,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,...not only harms your reputation, \Nbut causes you to adopt a lifestyle...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.28,0:16:46.56,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,...that will push you into a corner \Nfrom which you will never escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.90,0:16:49.94,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,We never fight others and \N risk our lives over money, power...{I split this line into two because it was a massive mouthful, but even after splitting, I still feel it's rather unwieldy... Not sure how to fix it though. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.94,0:16:57.78,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,...or even something as simple as \N having your seat taken at the theater or on a bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.78,0:17:02.04,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Fighting is a foolish game \N good only for preoccupying idiots. {Suggesting "only good" instead of "good only." -Axel}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.16,0:17:04.25,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.25,0:17:09.13,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,I would risk my life \N if my trust were abused.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.13,0:17:14.01,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,I believe that in such cases, \N God forgives even murder. {Deleted "a" after "such." Oh, almost forgot..... *bonk* -Axel}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.68,0:17:16.93,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Never forget that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.01,0:17:22.02,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Congratulations! \N I'm permitting you to join our organization! {he's reached peak enlightenment... or he literally farts rainbow sparkles}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.02,0:17:26.90,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Since you brought back the ignited lighter \N as I trusted you would...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.90,0:17:28.36,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,...you pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.03,0:17:38.41,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,This is the badge of our organization, Passione.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.12,0:17:41.79,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,A token proving you passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.37,0:17:46.75,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,For now, you're to operate \N under Buccellati's orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.73,0:18:06.56,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,How about it? \N Why don't we celebrate your...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.36,0:18:18.36,Thoughts,Polpo,0,0,0,,Did that kid really protect the flame \N for twenty-four hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.36,0:18:23.04,Thoughts,Polpo,0,0,0,,Or did he reignite it \N and become a Stand user? {this face}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.41,0:18:26.62,Thoughts,Polpo,0,0,0,,I suppose it doesn't matter either way. {only one a mother could... nah, she'd probably toss him in a dumpster}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.62,0:18:30.92,Thoughts,Polpo,0,0,0,,Clueless young boys like him \N are easy to manipulate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.25,0:18:35.21,Thoughts,Polpo,0,0,0,,Regardless of the outcome, \N we can use him as we please.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.68,0:18:43.76,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.47,0:18:47.27,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,I could have sworn I closed that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.15,0:18:53.23,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,The blood really does flow to my stomach \N after I've eaten...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.25,0:19:11.00,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,You encountered him again?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.00,0:19:13.21,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Mr. Jotaro...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.21,0:19:21.93,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,But I can't help but feel that Giorno Giovanna \N isn't as dangerous as you think he is. {Fixed typo. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.93,0:19:23.64,Narrator,Jotaro,0,0,0,,Why do you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.64,0:19:24.81,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.85,0:19:30.69,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Well, I'll tell you in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.69,0:19:32.27,Narrator,Koichi,0,0,0,,Is that okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.19,0:19:34.40,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.73,0:19:37.32,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,If that's what you prefer, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.32,0:19:39.07,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.07,0:19:41.03,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.03,0:19:42.24,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I'll talk to you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.16,0:19:48.95,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,Mr. Jotaro, for a while I really wondered...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.95,0:19:53.04,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,Could this Giorno kid \N really have such aspirations?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.04,0:19:55.17,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,Is he sane?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.17,0:19:57.59,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,But I can feel it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.59,0:20:00.63,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,I can tell he has a noble heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.34,0:20:03.72,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,I feel this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.34,0:20:09.81,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,...because of what I saw in the three men who carried \N the Joestar family blood in their veins back in Morioh. {Added "the" before "Joestar family blood." Your call if you want to delete it. -Axel}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.39,0:20:15.94,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,Those three whose righteous hearts \N could practically be called their energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.02,0:20:19.48,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,I saw it in his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.19,0:20:25.66,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, the blood that flows through his veins \N carries the will of the Joestars. {late parte 5 style bois}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.70,0:20:33.21,Thoughts,Koichi,0,0,0,,So for now, to respect his wishes, \N I'm going to shut away what he told me inside my heart... {I like this line. -Axel}
